    <briefdescription>
<para>A lightweight handle representing a unique identifier for traits. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="structDali_1_1Ui_1_1TraitId" kindref="compound">TraitId</ref> values are allocated sequentially via <ref refid="structDali_1_1Ui_1_1TraitId_1a4a999a087fb4b26075d549d72c4109e2" kindref="member">TraitId::Alloc()</ref>. Framework-reserved IDs are defined in the ReservedTraitId namespace. Extension or application code should allocate IDs with <ref refid="structDali_1_1Ui_1_1TraitId_1a4a999a087fb4b26075d549d72c4109e2" kindref="member">TraitId::Alloc()</ref> and store them in a static variable so each logical trait gets exactly one ID.</para>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>One-time<sp/>allocation<sp/>per<sp/>trait<sp/>type<sp/>(e.g.<sp/>in<sp/>an<sp/>anonymous<sp/>namespace<sp/>or<sp/>as<sp/>a<sp/>static)</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="keyword">static</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">const</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>TraitId<sp/>kMyScrollStateTrait<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="structDali_1_1Ui_1_1TraitId_1a4a999a087fb4b26075d549d72c4109e2" kindref="member">TraitId::Alloc</ref>();</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
    </detaileddescription>
